Name: KOFFING
Pokedex: The result of unifying poisonous gas, steam and a superheated atmosphere. Highly volatile, these Koffing are capable of spewing fireballs.

Name: WEEZING
Pokedex: The superheated atmosphere of a volcano makes their chemical composition far more unstable and likely to attract more gaseous tumours on its body.

Name: SOLOSIS
Pokedex: They do not like light and are found in dark waters. They use their remote psychic ability to find food to sustain itself.

Name: DUOSION
Pokedex: It exhibited significant psychic potential when it was just a single-celled organism. Imagine the power it possesses now that it has evolved.

Name: REUNICLUS
Pokedex: These Pokemon are capable of bending water to its will and forming fantastic water sculptures with its mind.

Name: GASTLY
Pokedex: Whenever hail falls, you can likely credit a Gastly as being responsible for starting it.

Name: HAUNTER
Pokedex: Haunters are mischievous creatures. Their command of ice allows them to set up icy traps for unsuspecting passerbys.

Name: GENGAR
Pokedex: Due to its mastery of cloud systems, Gengars are capable of summoning powerful hailstorms and blizzards at will.

Name: DODUO
Pokedex: It can channel the power of the night sky into its attacks. It forgoes physical violence in favour of attacking from afar with its nascent mind.

Name: DODRIO
Pokedex: It is rumoured that each of its heads are simultaneously looking into different timelines and universes to anticipate enemy attacks.

Name: EKANS
Pokedex: The rhythmic sound of an Ekans's tail is enough to put its foe to sleep when it can then move in to consume it whole.

Name: ARBOK
Pokedex: The poison of an Arbok is so corrosive that it can melt steel beams. It is able to manipulate the face on its body into different shapes to fool its prey.

Name: STARYU
Pokedex: They are commonly found in caves, rich in ore and other minerals. Its body is translucent and light to the touch.

Name: STARMIE
Pokedex: It is often mistaken for precious gems because it is able to change its appearance to suit every colour of the rainbow.

Name: ONIX
Pokedex: It can easily blend itself into the surroundings of a glacier. Some explorers have confused sudden movement of a glacier with the movement of an Onix.

Name: STEELIX
Pokedex: It has mastered the power of the ice around it that it can materialize large ice projectiles and launch them at its foes.

Name: SLUGMA
Pokedex: It is a species of PokÃ©mon that lives and feeds in areas full of toxic waste. It can ooze into multiple several autonomous parts, albeit slowly.

Name: MAGCARGO
Pokedex: The shell on its back is made of discarded material that it has absorbed into its skin while feeding. Its greatest threat is its ability to multiply.

Name: WAILMER
Pokedex: It was young and defenseless when it was killed by poachers. Now it roams the seas, always crying out in anguish as it relives its pain.

Name: WAILORD
Pokedex: Its body has started to decompose, exuding a foul odour which betrays its ability to hunt down the poachers that killed it and seek vengeance.

Name: FLETCHLING
Pokedex: As a small immature bird, it has not yet learned to control its built-in electricity and will sometimes periodically shock itself as it learns.

Name: FLETCHINDER
Pokedex: It is very territorial and can be reckless as it matures. As a young upstart, its ability to use electricity has made it impulsive and overconfident.

Name: TALONFLAME
Pokedex: Its favoured techniques is to charge itself up with electricity and dive into an enemy. The damage it deals is far more significant than the damage it sustains.

Name: NATU
Pokedex: Aerial Tactical Unit, Model N, or N-ATU. is used by espionage and military for small surveillance and reconnaissance missions.

Name: XATU
Pokedex: Far deadlier than Model N, Model X-ATU is an offensive drone, capable of carrying multiple payloads used for destroying remote bases from a distance.

Name: RUFFLET
Pokedex: It is just learning to spit fire. As it matures, the fire becomes hotter and more intense.

Name: BRAVIARY
Pokedex: When they are reaching the end of its life, this Pokemon will fly away to be reborn into an egg in isolation. No one has seen this to confirm though.

Name: NOSEPASS
Pokedex: It travels in small hunting parties and use shrill voices to signal when it finds trouble. They mutter to each other in unintelligible growls.

Name: PROBOPASS
Pokedex: It is seen as a spiritual elder within its local tribe because its psychic potential allows it to command the respect and obedience of its compatriots.

Name: ZUBAT
Pokedex: They are naughty Pokemon and often will pull pranks on travelers passing by in their cave.

Name: GOLBAT
Pokedex: Its teeth are much sharper and are capable of draining blood. It is known for its rapid speed and stealth.

Name: CROBAT
Pokedex: The edges of its wings are as sharp as steel and when it dives headfirst after reaching maximum velocity, it is capable of slicing its target clean in half.

Name: TANGELA
Pokedex: Despite its appearance, it is very lightweight. It is very susceptible to strong breezes and can be knocked around easily.

Name: TANGROWTH
Pokedex: After constantly being tossed around in the harsh desert winds, it has grown in mass and can sometimes found to be holding water.

Name: TYMPOLE
Pokedex: It has spent too much time near the water's edge such that it has started to grow mushrooms.

Name: PALPITOAD
Pokedex: As it started to migrate further inland into swamp areas, mushrooms began to grow on its damp body and has now become inseparable from its skin.

Name: SEISMITOAD
Pokedex: The mushrooms have become so prevalent and grown in potency that simply touching them can render a person incapacitated.

Name: GULPIN
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon's small stature and colour allows it to camoflage in desert environments to protect itself from predators.

Name: SWALOT
Pokedex: It is much larger than it appears. That is because it can disperse and consume the sand around it to grow in mass.

Name: SPINARAK
Pokedex: It can spin elaborate webs with different pictures in the webs. It uses these pictures to attract prey where it traps them and then allows them to be consumed.

Name: ARIADOS
Pokedex: Its most terrifying quality is its ability to vanish into darkness and surprise its foe by sinking its poisonous fangs into its target.

Name: BALTOY
Pokedex: It is jointly powered by both an electrical current and its psychic potential. It emanates an aura of psychic prowess.

Name: CLAYDOL
Pokedex: Because it is able to detach itself using its psychic powers, but still control its limbs, it is able to mitigate damage to it and use surprise attacks.

Name: ZORUA
Pokedex: They are very loyal creatures and can hunt in small packs. Due to their loyalty, they are subservient to the alpha of each pack.

Name: ZOROARK
Pokedex: The strongest and fastest hunter becomes the alpha and then eventually evolves into the Zoroark leader of the pack.

Name: DUCKLETT
Pokedex: It is said that its feathers bring good luck. It honks several times if it is happy similar to a dog wagging its tail.

Name: SWANNA
Pokedex: It is endangered because its feathers allegedly grant you a wish, but only if it gives you the feather of its own volition.

Name: GOLETT
Pokedex: These PokÃ©mon are thought to have come to the Orion Region through a meteorite from outer space as evidenced by their extra-terrestrial colour.

Name: GOLURK
Pokedex: It is said that their cores are time capsules and if anyone opens them, they could unlock secrets that were stored there by a destroyed civilization.

Name: MORELULL
Pokedex: Its illuminating ability mixed with volcanic ash infected it, making its skin poisonous to the touch.

Name: SHIINOTIC
Pokedex: These kinds of Shiinotic truly live a miserable existence as they constantly cough up ash.

Name: LARVESTA
Pokedex: You can often find this Pokemon nibbling on electric wires to siphon the electrical current within as food.

Name: VOLCARONA
Pokedex: When it flaps its wings furiously, it can send electrical currents through the air which it uses to hunt down and chase its prey.

Name: STANTLER
Pokedex: Various berries form a key element of a Stantler's diet. They enjoy them so much that their antlers grow some of their own during the autumn season.

Name: MAGIKARP
Pokedex: This Pokemon is found only in deep water where the current tends to be weaker. It uses its antennae to attract prey.

Name: GYARADOS
Pokedex: It is able to sense movement in the water and can swim quietly. It keeps its eyes closed right up until it opens its mouth to consume its prey.

Name: BERGMITE
Pokedex: It is made of extra jagged rock so when it launches itself in full-body tackles at its enemy, it can pierce and significantly damage them.

Name: AVALUGG
Pokedex: Because it was formed in the earth's core, it has no trouble navigating because of its built-in magnetism.

Name: LEDYBA
Pokedex: Due to their small size and bug-like appearance, they are often used by spy agencies to remotely observe targets or persons of interest.

Name: LEDIAN
Pokedex: When discovered, they can beat its wings to emit a high-frequency screeching noise to deafen and distract to allow it enough time to escape.

Name: PONYTA
Pokedex: It runs so fast that it looks like it disappears into shadow only to return with a blaze.

Name: RAPIDASH
Pokedex: It is the loyal steed of a fallen hero. It burns with fiery passion from the grave as it seeks vengeance for its master's killer.

Name: AMAURA
Pokedex: It accompanies people that are lost in nightmares back to safety and away from danger. It uses its abilities to shield sleeping people from evil forces.

Name: AURORUS
Pokedex: Apparently, it is able to walk seamlessly between the waking world and the dream realm. Anyone seeing it while fast asleep will have good luck for a year.

Name: GEODUDE
Pokedex: Its body is hot to the touch as it was recently formed from magma floes. Simply touching it can cause second degree burns.

Name: GRAVELER
Pokedex: Its eyes flare with fiery power when it gets mad. Deep within it, it carries the power of a volcano and it is highly unstable. Do not anger at any cost.

Name: GOLEM
Pokedex: The volcanic power that it tries to keep under control has started to seep through its skin. It uses this lava to quickly cauterize flesh wounds.

Name: SKRELP
Pokedex: It is able to change its pigment colour to camouflage within beds of seaweed so that it is able to easily harvest and feed on algae on the sea floor.

Name: DRAGALGE
Pokedex: Its fins are made of seaweed so it is very limber and much faster. However, as a result, it is far more susceptible to physical damage.

Name: LITLEO
Pokedex: From an early age, they are able to hunt on the snowy plains. Their fur allows them to blend into the snow making them excellent predators.

Name: PYROAR
Pokedex: A pride of Pyroars typically consist of one alpha male and several females. They are nomadic and frequently migrate across snowy plains in search of food.

Name: LUNATONE
Pokedex: It is said to have come from a comet that breached the Earth's atmosphere. It emits a powerful frozen aura when it senses danger.

Name: SOLROCK
Pokedex: It was formed in the heart of a volcano. It emanates a flame aura that can scorch anyone that wanders nearby.

Name: DROWZEE
Pokedex: It is a brutish Pokemon that will fight others in its tribe for scraps of meat. It gets easily irritated and always resorts to violence.

Name: HYPNO
Pokedex: It carries around a pendant as a trophy. It is a grossly unpleasant creature as it both farts and snores loudly.

Name: SEEL
Pokedex: It lazes about on small islands when it tires of diving for food. It spends most of its day eating and sleeping.

Name: DEWGONG
Pokedex: It is exceptionally heavy, but it is able to fend off predators with its long horn.

Name: SKIDDO
Pokedex: It is very territorial and typically battles others in its herd from a young age, to sharpen its horn and assert dominance among its peers.

Name: GOGOAT
Pokedex: They have developed techniques to headbutt mountains and walls to toughen their horns and are very adept at scaling mountains.

Name: KABUTO
Pokedex: Swarms of these locust Pokemon have been known for being able to devour fields of crops in minutes.

Name: KABUTOPS
Pokedex: Its hunting ability is unparalleled. It is able to lie in wait silently for its prey and then use its sickles to finish the job.

Name: SHROOMISH
Pokedex: It was used in civil wars and planted in the jungle where rebels would hide. Due to its unsuspecting appearance, many rebels would step on them and set off the mine.

Name: BRELOOM
Pokedex: It is frequently used as security because when intruders are identified, it emits a loud screeching noise.

Name: AERODACTYL
Pokedex: Its greenish tint is said to have come from this species flying in especially humid, jungly areas.

Name: ROGGENROLA
Pokedex: Each one that forms is said to have come from massive glaciers that existed several hundred years ago.

Name: BOLDORE
Pokedex: Due to the ongoing climate crisis, parts of icebergs that have since melted and separated away turn into Boldores.

Name: GIGALITH
Pokedex: Many inattentive sailors have come to their doom when their ships have collided with these Pokemon out on the frozen seas.

Name: FINNEON
Pokedex: Depending on the temperature of the water it swims in, the colour of its body and fins will change accordingly.

Name: LUMINEON
Pokedex: It changes the colour of the eye design that it has on its sides to attract mates. This pattern can also be used to blind pursuing predators.

Name: GLIGAR
Pokedex: It can enter into a state of perfect stillness that it can fool people into thinking it is really a statue.

Name: GLISCOR
Pokedex: Late at night, they are known to congregate on rooftops, but do not count on seeing them move during the daytime.

Name: LILLIPUP
Pokedex: Left to fend for itself, its vital spirit and resilience allowed it to survive but it lacks trust in humans after initially being abandoned.

Name: HERDIER
Pokedex: Forced to survive on its own, it has submitted fully to its feral instinct and can be difficult to tame.

Name: STOUTLAND
Pokedex: The spirit of a Stoutland that passed away after abuse and starvation. Even death will not give this Pokemon peace and rest.

Name: DRIFLOON
Pokedex: The fact that it is filled with helium makes it very lightweight and prone to fly off into the wind unless restrained down to the ground.

Name: DRIFBLIM
Pokedex: The hot air that is used to power it and help it move can burn a person if they get too close.

Name: MINCCINO
Pokedex: After this Minccino was abused during its life, its spirit has come back and taken up a doll as its host in hopes of finding a better owner.

Name: CINCCINO
Pokedex: This Cinccino uses any random buttons it can find to cover up its eye because it still thinks it is alive and needs to conceal its abuse.

Name: BONSLY
Pokedex: It can be found near other cacti as a flower growing in an otherwise desolate environment.

Name: SUDOWOODO
Pokedex: It masquerades as a cactus and its thorns can pierce skin with just the smallest poke.

Name: DRUDDIGON
Pokedex: It has forgone its ability to fly in exchange for developing jagged spikes on its back and as such, now largely resides in dark caves.

Name: WOOBAT
Pokedex: Its fangs are extra sharp to enable this Pokemon to pierce the skin of its target and drain its blood quickly.

Name: SWOOBAT
Pokedex: It is very sensitive to light. Some say that it does not produce a reflection, but most people say that is just a myth.

Name: KRABBY
Pokedex: They look like harmless sandy rocks while disguised, but when stepped on, they will furiously chase you to pinch you back.

Name: KINGLER
Pokedex: It is highly versatile as it is able to use its massive pincers to handle and crush rocks like opposable thumbs.

Name: HOOTHOOT
Pokedex: Found most often in wintry climates, it keeps itself warm with its lunar aura it emits rather than its feathers.

Name: NOCTOWL
Pokedex: It uses its psychic powers to replicate the auroras that can be seen in northern areas of the Orion Region.

Name: VOLTORB
Pokedex: It is often confused as being a snowball which has resulted in many instances of small children throwing them at others.

Name: ELECTRODE
Pokedex: It was formerly the head of a snowman a small child carelessly discarded after they were done playing in the snow.

Name: SANDYGAST
Pokedex: The toque is the closest thing it has to a friend because when it tries to befriend children, they run away in fear.

Name: PALOSSAND
Pokedex: It disguises itself as a snow castle in hopes of attracting children to play with it. When they get close enough, it will consume them.

Name: WEEDLE
Pokedex: No one will ever suspect an innocuous looking Weedle until it is too late to realize that it has been planting remote surveillance spy bots everywhere.

Name: KAKUNA
Pokedex: It is used for surveillance measures and employs an innocuous Kakuna disguise to avoid attracting attention.

Name: BEEDRILL
Pokedex: All of its time spent observing its enemies while in its earlier stages have helped it learn such that it now preys on those that once hunted it.

Name: MACHOP
Pokedex: With its one eye, it lacks a spatial sense but what it lacks in this sense, it makes up for through brute strength.

Name: MACHOKE
Pokedex: It is prone to entering into a rage when it loses things. The fact that it has only one eye to find lost articles does not help either.

Name: MACHAMP
Pokedex: The addition of its two extra arms has somehow made it even more disoriented than it was previously. However, it hits harder as a result.

Name: BULBASAUR
Pokedex: They are attracted to shiny crystals and seek nourishment from sapping the energy of other crystals to empower the one on its own back.

Name: IVYSAUR
Pokedex: It has become so deeply intertwined with its crystal that any poacher that seeks to take its crystal will inevitably kill this creature too.

Name: VENUSAUR
Pokedex: It is able to make the various crystals on its back turn into different colours as a way of attracting mates.

Name: TAUROS
Pokedex: It is incredibly fast and strong. It can charge into walls with reckless abandon.

Name: CARVANHA
Pokedex: It is capable of breaking the speed of sound quite easily. It is able to dodge and evade enemy missiles easily.

Name: SHARPEDO
Pokedex: It is capable of close combat or attacking from afar. It depends on the commander's purpose and whether the Pokemon is expendable or not.

Name: TIMBURR
Pokedex: The stuff of nightmares; this Pokemon has affixed a blunt instrument on the end of its slab of wood to use as a weapon.

Name: GURDURR
Pokedex: It changes its makeup to match the same as what was worn by its last victim.

Name: CONKELDURR
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon was part of the circus and abused by the circus master. The trails of blood on its columns are of the deceased circus master.

Name: LITWICK
Pokedex: When a Litwick possesses a lightbulb, it is said that it drains its power more rapidly to heal itself.

Name: LAMPENT
Pokedex: It possesses street lights and pranks municipal workers into thinking the lamp light has fused. It then scares the workers when they come to repair them.

Name: CHANDELURE
Pokedex: The spirit possessed a chandelier and now pranks people by turning on and off rapidly to create a more menacing atmosphere.

Name: VANILLITE
Pokedex: Whether this Pokemon was created from raw toxic waste found in dumping grounds or was already there is a mystery.

Name: VANILLISH
Pokedex: It's unknown where exactly the Pokemon ends and the trail of sludge begins. There is a suspicion that it varies from one to another.

Name: VANILLUXE
Pokedex: The suspicion is that the mass of toxic waste belonging to this Pokemon is much larger than originally believed.

Name: ELEKID
Pokedex: Its antennae hum when a predator is nearby. Its natural inclination is to fight the predator rather than flee.

Name: ELECTABUZZ
Pokedex: It has no fear, and will willingly take on enemies much larger and stronger in size without flinching. Arguably, this can be seen as both a strength and a weakness.

Name: ELECTIVIRE
Pokedex: It will fight any foe as every fight, regardless of the outcome, is a learning moment that it uses to get stronger.

Name: POPPLIO
Pokedex: Its collar is made from petals. The colour of the collar is said to change with the seasons.

Name: BRIONNE
Pokedex: Its mere presence is said to have restorative properties and can cleanse toxins out of the air.

Name: PRIMARINA
Pokedex: It is said that as it grows older, the petals of the rose on its head will begin to wilt. When the final petal falls, this Pokemon passes away.

Name: SNORUNT
Pokedex: It is found in large numbers in tombs and crypts. They will often remain motionless and then mass attack grave robbers.

Name: GLALIE
Pokedex: It gets incredibly agitated when it is confused for a rock.

Name: FROSLASS
Pokedex: It hovers around tombs and crypts in search of any visitors, hoping to drain its soul and add the corpse to the graveyard.

Name: MAGBY
Pokedex: It can often be found swimming about near glaciers and melting ice caps. It is able to dive deep into the ocean floor.

Name: MAGMAR
Pokedex: It can be found both on frozen tundra, glaciers and in frozen oceans roaming in isolation.

Name: MAGMORTAR
Pokedex: It likes to sink ice breaker ships by blasting them with solid chunks of ice. It has caused millions in damages to local governments.

Name: EXEGGCUTE
Pokedex: This Pokemon was created as a consequence of a nuclear fallout. It's not clear what it looked like prior to this event.

Name: EXEGGUTOR
Pokedex: It is said that prolonged exposure to this Pokemon can cause illness due to the nuclear radiation it emanates.

Name: JOLTIK
Pokedex: It is said these Pokemon don't actually appear in real life but are mere instances of your worst nightmares manifesting in reality.

Name: GALVANTULA
Pokedex: This creature represents one's deepest and darkest fears made real. Its stinger can lull people into a deep sleep where it feasts on their sanity.

Name: GRIMER
Pokedex: It is found deep in swampy areas. When you find yourself in sinking mud, it is most likely a Grimer holding onto you.

Name: MUK
Pokedex: It is rumoured to guard swamps and appear in deep fog. The sound of its movements are often confused as wailing, giving it the title of Swamp Creature.

Name: CHIMCHAR
Pokedex: Because of its size and speed, it can dash very quickly that it almost appears to be teleporting from one place to another.

Name: MONFERNO
Pokedex: Due to its speed, it is able to create illusions of itself that can encircle and confuse a foe.

Name: INFERNAPE
Pokedex: It uses its bo staff to enable it to land multiple blows on its foe. When the foe comes to retaliate, it is able to zap away.

Name: SABLEYE
Pokedex: It lives in volcanic environments. The hotter the environment, the more at home it feels.

Name: CUBCHOO
Pokedex: It is in constant competition with Slowpoke for honey and other shiny things. Its cuteness allows it to dodge consequences from its theft.

Name: BEARTIC
Pokedex: It is very irritable when it is awoken from sleep. It can go on rampages when it is hungry.

Name: TREECKO
Pokedex: It is able to lay perfectly still for hours and blend into the environment. It lies in wait until its prey steps upon its trap and then handily disposes of its foe.

Name: GROVYLE
Pokedex: It has a long tongue that it uses to quickly swallow up smaller insects and has the ability to fan the spikes on its body out at predators.

Name: SCEPTILE
Pokedex: It is able to shimmer its tail in a rhythmic pattern to distract foes. During the night time, its compound eyes allow it to increase its vision range.

Name: LARVITAR
Pokedex: It is frequently posted as sentries around high-security zones. It uses a mix of antennae and sonar signals to reveal hidden enemies.

Name: PUPITAR
Pokedex: When it gets angry, it starts to overheat. Its inventor anticipated the need to create several exhaust vents to provide it ample avenues to let off heat.

Name: TYRANITAR
Pokedex: It moves slowly and finds it difficult to navigate due to its reinforced steel plating. Its shielding is almost impenetrable.

Name: HIPPOPOTAS
Pokedex: It is able to jump into puddles and rapidly absorb the water up. For this reason, they are used frequently to clean up spills.

Name: HIPPOWDON
Pokedex: The tree on its back renders its ability to hide from predators moot, so it has learned to defend itself by being very aggressive.

Name: BRONZOR
Pokedex: It was once used to guard sacred temples and ruins. Over time, the effects of weather have worn away at it and vines have grown over it.

Name: BRONZONG
Pokedex: Some say this Pokemon was once an idol that early civilizations prayed to so it would bring rain and crops would be allowed to grow.

Name: SWIRLIX
Pokedex: It is lightweight and easily blown around by a strong breeze. It enjoys travelling in small packs so that they can bounce off one another in strong winds.

Name: SLURPUFF
Pokedex: It is said that the feathers from its wings grant wishes, so they are highly sought after Pokemon.

Name: MAREEP
Pokedex: Its wool actually makes it weigh less overall eventually allowing it to become airborne.

Name: FLAAFFY
Pokedex: Its wool is made of cotton candy. It is said that if you eat some, it will give you wings.

Name: AMPHAROS
Pokedex: Its wings are also made of cotton candy, and will often give passengers some of them to cheer them up.

Name: SWABLU
Pokedex: After flying through sulfuric clouds, it slowly became infected with them, which has made it sluggish when flying.

Name: ALTARIA
Pokedex: It is a mystery whether it is the cause of the pollution or just happens to have absorbed the pollution within its habitat.

Name: ABRA
Pokedex: It meditates for most of the day. Most observers believe it to be asleep but its spirit has transcended to a plane of enlightenment.

Name: KADABRA
Pokedex: It trains its fists both through repetitive attacks against hard surfaces and also against ethereal forces as regular training.

Name: ALAKAZAM
Pokedex: Its Nunchakus are an extension of its arms. It has learned to use them seamlessly and flawlessly.

Name: VENIPEDE
Pokedex: A Venipede happened upon a meteorite that had special powers thereby giving it extraterrestrial powers.

Name: WHIRLIPEDE
Pokedex: The meteorite that it discovered has enabled it to move things with its mind. The rock is now more in control of the host body than the original Whirlipede.

Name: SCOLIPEDE
Pokedex: The original meteorite that controlled this Pokemon becomes simultaneously aware and is able to act in unison with other Scolipedes.

Name: HERACROSS
Pokedex: During mating season, the more shapelier one's ball of dung is, the more impressive it is to potential mates.

Name: TEDDIURSA
Pokedex: The degree of transparency in its body follows the lunar cycle. During full moons, it is fully corporeal while during new moons, it is fully ethereal.

Name: URSARING
Pokedex: It is said that when this Pokemon passes away, its body rejoins the cosmos as a new star.

Name: PSYDUCK
Pokedex: The gem on its head is capable of allowing it to see briefly into the future, which allows it to anticipate attacks.

Name: GOLDUCK
Pokedex: It has a soothing aura that it emanates that is capable of cleansing toxic environments.

Name: DUSKULL
Pokedex: The flame that burns in its soul is enough to absorb the life force of anyone that wanders too close to it.

Name: DUSCLOPS
Pokedex: It is said that anyone that manages to touch its eye will be maimed with third degree burns.

Name: DUSKNOIR
Pokedex: It is capable of basking its entire body in flame and recklessly charging the enemy.

Name: SKITTY
Pokedex: An evil spirit that was being hunted quickly possessed a nearby Skitty due to the latter being a relatively easy target.

Name: DELCATTY
Pokedex: When the Skitty that was possessed by an evil spirit evolved, this made the latent spirit stronger and more demonic.

Name: T.EEVEE
Pokedex: This Pokemon was subjected to cruelty in life which has affected its unstable genetic makeup, allowing it to evolve into different variations.

Name: T.VAPOREON
Pokedex: It is a very shy Pokemon and when it spots humans, it is quick to retreat back into deep sands.

Name: T.JOLTEON
Pokedex: The storm clouds that circle it are very unstable and it is still learning how to fully control and master the energy it produces.

Name: T.FLAREON
Pokedex: The drill on its tail is heavily rusted, which slows it down significantly. However, the drill is sharp and very corrosive which helps it defend itself.

Name: T.ESPEON
Pokedex: Its tail is drenched in highly corrosive poison, and it is unable to control when to poison anyone that touches it, rendering it untouchable to many.

Name: T.UMBREON
Pokedex: It has been trained as a vigilante and seeks out justice for those that have been subjected to cruelty or misfortune at the hands of others.

Name: T.LEAFEON
Pokedex: Its wing-like membrane is sticky, allowing it to fly through the air and catch smaller insects in them for it to feed on.

Name: T.GLACEON
Pokedex: It adorns itself in gems in a futile attempt to deceive trainers into loving it. This however has led to it being hunted for its valuable minerals.

Name: T.SYLVEON
Pokedex: Its rage is so palpable that the colour of its ribbons change colour to replicate the state of its emotion. It is almost impossible to soothe.

Name: DEERLING
Pokedex: Its flames flare up when it is either in distress or very happy, making it difficult to properly understand and care for.

Name: SAWSBUCK
Pokedex: Its footsteps can easily start a fire, which make it a serious danger to forest habitats where it is most prevalent.

Name: ARON
Pokedex: It is capable of burrowing deep underground and building large, sprawling nests where they breed and can quickly spread.

Name: LAIRON

Pokedex: Sometimes found in rocky, mountainous regions, they are adept mountain climbers and can scale uneven terrains with ease.

Name: CHARIZARD
Pokedex: Its skin is very oily. It is unclear what substance hangs off its wings, as any previous attempts to harvest some have angered it greatly.

Name: MAGNEMITE
Pokedex: It is sent out by the primary Magnezone mothership as a small observer to study certain environments, take samples and return.

Name: MAGNETON
Pokedex: It is capable of taking high-quality photography with its lenses which make it very useful for studying certain environments.

Name: MAGNEZONE
Pokedex: When it has found a planet worth studying, it will instruct smaller Magnemite and Magnetons to surveil and relay information back to it.

Name: REGIROCK
Pokedex: It can disperse into smaller cloud systems at will. When it reforms, it can cause a thunder storm in the area.

Name: REGICE
Pokedex: It was once a spirit that inhabited a very old tree but has transferred from tree to tree to save itself when cut down by loggers.

Name: REGISTEEL
Pokedex: A person that stares into the mystery of its orb will either find fortune or curse themselves and drive themselves to madness.

Name: SPEAROW
Pokedex: It hunts in small flocks and will chatter among themselves to cooperate and signal to one another when they have found a source of food.

Name: FEAROW
Pokedex: It hunts out at sea and in oceans. It will dive into the water from a distance to pick up a fish Pokemon such as an Arrokuda when it is hungry.

Name: IGGLYBUFF
Pokedex: This Pokemon can manifest wherever water can be found... from the depths of the ocean, to a kitchen sink. They are very small in size so almost unnoticeable.

Name: JIGGLYPUFF
Pokedex: When it gets angry, it huffs and puffs to make itself bigger to show it means business. Often though, many people do not take it seriously.

Name: WIGGLYTUFF
Pokedex: This Pokemon has grown to such a size that it is able to blow bubbles of its own. This is one method it has to actually create more Igglybuffs.

Name: VULLABY
Pokedex: It does not matter that a Vullaby may have hatched many months ago, it still carries the egg shell that it was born in around as pants.

Name: MANDIBUZZ
Pokedex: They circle around dying Pokemon in rough terrain. When the Pokemon finally dies, the Mandibuzz are first to help themselves to the remains.

Name: SHINX
Pokedex: It is unable to use its wings to fly long distances quite yet, but they are able to float in the air for short periods by flapping them fiercely.

Name: LUXIO
Pokedex: Because its wings are not fully developed, it relies on its speed and toxic fangs to protect itself from would-be predators.

Name: LUXRAY
Pokedex: Their wings are strong and fully developed so they can fly large distances with a single flap. Their toxic fangs are similarly exceptionally deadly.

Name: ELECTRIKE
Pokedex: It wears a skull of an animal it scavenged as a sort of trophy to protect itself. No one has actually seen what it looks like under the skull.

Name: MANECTRIC
Pokedex: When it evolved, the skull it scavenged as an Electrike became a part of its features, that they can no longer be independently removed.

Name: FERROSEED
Pokedex: It camouflages well into its surroundings. It uses its beautiful flowers to attract prey and will then bring them down through a volley of thorns.

Name: FERROTHORN
Pokedex: It subtly uses the flowers on its head to attract certain prey. When the prey close in, it can jump up and consume them in a single gulp.

Name: MAREANIE
Pokedex: This deceitful Pokemon pretends to be nothing more than a shrub to catch its prey off-guard. It oozes one of the most lethal poisons in the world.

Name: TOXAPEX
Pokedex: Riddled with malice and anger, this Pokemon tries to cause as much pain as possible to its foes using its potent venom.

Name: SWINUB
Pokedex: Rubbing its fur first can make you give off static electricity.

Name: PILOSWINE
Pokedex: Its fur is exceptionally warm and are often found in rocky areas where they graze on small grassy patches.

Name: MAMOSWINE
Pokedex: Because of the charges on its fur, its tusks are always sparking with a degree of residual static electricity as the charges seek out a way to escape.

Name: TORKOAL
Pokedex: Despite being a storm cloud, it is often found hovering around high altitude environments such as mountainous regions.

Name: TURTWIG
Pokedex: The volcanic formation on its back is relatively immature so the embers that are still hardening are very hot and occasionally smoke.

Name: GROTLE
Pokedex: The volcanic formation on its back has hardened but there are small vents that have created that allow the built in heat to periodically escape.

Name: TORTERRA
Pokedex: It is recommended to keep a short distance away as the volcanic formation on its back periodically releases short bouts of lava and smoke.

Name: BUNEARY
Pokedex: This little bunny is headed for stardom! It practices every day until it perfects its technique, which then allows it to evolve into a real star.

Name: LOPUNNY
Pokedex: This Pokemon is very competitive by nature. Do not try to steal its thunder as they become enraged very easily!

Name: DITTO
Pokedex: A species that is the subject of intense study by researchers. Some say that it is matter that came from outer space.

Name: PHIONE
Pokedex: Whenever a person requests a wish from a Manaphy, a Phione is rumoured to be created as a result.

Name: T.MANAPHY
Pokedex: This Pokemon can grant three wishes to any person that is able to capture it.

Name: DARKRAI
Pokedex: This Pokemon is rumoured to be a prophet and is worshipped due to its ability to see the future.

Name: CRESSELIA
Pokedex: Cresselia is supposed to be empowered by any toxic environments and thrives in wastelands and other diseased areas.

Name: BUIZEL
Pokedex: This Pokemon is able to use the small turbine on its tail to quickly wade through polluted waters and cleanse them of impurities.

Name: FLOATZEL
Pokedex: Designed to help filter out pollution from water, the blue sphere at the centre of its stomach turns to brown when its filter is full and requires emptying.

Name: BUDEW
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon is reluctant to fight, and when confronted, it would rather run away quickly than get its outfit dirty.

Name: ROSELIA
Pokedex: It can execute moves and dances with eloquence that invokes confidence and inspiration among those privileged to watch it fight.

Name: ROSERADE
Pokedex: This Pokemon prefers to conceal its identity and prefers to pose with its face covered as much as possible.

Name: KLEFKI
Pokedex: It is a traditional Pokemon that is endowed with a number of protective charms and enchantments that help it shield their owner from evil spirits.

Name: DEWPIDER
Pokedex: It flickers when it is upset or emotional. It will turn the light it emits off when it is in danger so predators cannot pursue it.

Name: ARAQUANID
Pokedex: It moves around with noisy clacking sounds because its legs do not allow it to retain much gracefulness or be able to sneak up on people.

Name: T.GOTHITA
Pokedex: When it is angered, it will hiss and shoot petrifying gazes at the subject of their anger to temporarily immobilize them.

Name: T.GOTHORITA
Pokedex: The rattling sound its tail produces will often intensify when it finds prey, betraying its ability to hunt effectively.

Name: T.GOTHITELLE
Pokedex: It spits venomous fluid at its enemies that can corrode and slow down their foe. If it makes eye contact with you, it could also turn you to stone.

Name: TYRUNT
Pokedex: Despite its body being freezing cold to the touch, it is unclear how it is able to simultaneously have flames burning perpetually.

Name: TYRANTRUM
Pokedex: Its flames burn with a violent passion but the snow that has collected on its back never seems to melt. It is unclear how this is possible.

Name: CUBONE
Pokedex: It wields some of the surviving coral from the reefs it inhabits as a weapon to ward off foes.

Name: MAROWAK
Pokedex: Its helmet allows it to breathe underwater. However, it's not known if the coral reefs it is often found in is its natural habitat or not.

Name: T.SPRITZEE
Pokedex: It likes to carry around a lot of gold and shiny objects, although it's not clear how it does this given its small size.

Name: T.AROMATISSE
Pokedex: When it finds gold, it eats it, making its body larger. However, it is not clear if it is actually eating it or storing it as it is able to retrieve the gold at any time?

Name: T.HORSEA
Pokedex: It is responsible for pollinating many flowers in local fields and forests. When they do so, you can hear a loud buzzing noise.

Name: T.SEADRA
Pokedex: They roam around in small swarms to appear more threatening. They are capable of applying some deadly stings to anyone that irritates them.

Name: T.KINGDRA
Pokedex: When it flaps its wings, it is able to pollinate an entire field of flowers all at once, as such they are often used to repair damage ecosystems.

Name: CUTIEFLY
Pokedex: It is so small that it is sometimes hard to see them. However, they are very quick and difficult to hit unless you have a specialized swatter.

Name: RIBOMBEE
Pokedex: It hovers around dirty, urban areas most often. One of its favourite locations is the Orion Landfill.

Name: OMANYTE
Pokedex: It can use its magical hat to perform tricks. It is also capable of stepping into the hat and disappearing but it is not clear where it goes or how it comes back.

Name: OMASTAR
Pokedex: Its famous trick is to put Pokemon in the hat to make them disappear. It is not clear where the Pokemon goes or how it returns.

Name: SKWOVET
Pokedex: It often perches itself on frozen over trees to nibble on the fruits or leaves that have frozen over.

Name: GREEDENT
Pokedex: It hibernates in summer and emerges during winter. It prefers colder environments where it can easily find frozen food.

Name: T.GRIMER
Pokedex: This Pokemon appears in volcanically active areas. It can lob hot lava formed from its body from a distance to singe and immobilize enemies.

Name: T.MUK
Pokedex: When it opens its mouth to breathe, you can feel a large expulsion of hot air that will coat your entire body in sweat.

Name: PHANPY
Pokedex: This Pokemon likes to curl into a ball and toboggan down snowy hills in races against others of its herd.

Name: DONPHAN
Pokedex: Their woolly coat is highly sought after in the fashion world, but this has driven them to the point of near extinction because of irresponsible poachers.

Name: PIKIPEK
Pokedex: They are very messy birds and will frequently make nests in the roofs of hotels or resorts where numerous tourists frequent.

Name: TRUMBEAK
Pokedex: A vile nuisance, these Pokemon like to pick on unsuspecting tourists by carpet bombing their vehicles while they are relaxing on the beach.

Name: TOUCANNON
Pokedex: They are typically very aggressive and will outright steal food out of unsuspecting touristsâ€™ hands and then mock you after outsmarting you.

Name: PINECO
Pokedex: Miners need to be careful not to hit a Pineco as precious ores and gems are often found encrusted in the rocky surface of its skin.

Name: FORRETRESS
Pokedex: When you see a collection of precious minerals encrusted in the surface of the cave, it is a tell-tale sign that it is really a Forretress.

Name: T.HOOTHOOT
Pokedex: It is able to tilt its head 270 degrees. It uses this as a means of being able to scan its full surroundings.

Name: T.NOCTOWL
Pokedex: Its eyes are trained to be able to easily see through snow storms and strong blizzards.

Name: STUFFUL
Pokedex: This Pokemon has haunted a carelessly discarded stuffed animal and enjoys scaring ungrateful or bratty children.

Name: BEWEAR
Pokedex: Parts of its body that were hanging together have torn further at its seams, revealing part of the ghost that possesses it.

Name: CARBINK
Pokedex: Despite its small size, it is incredibly dense, exhibiting a gravitational force that it is able to attract small particles of rocks and mud to orbit around it.

Name: GIBLE
Pokedex: When travelers complain about a spectral force or report hearing growling noises or some sort of sinister aura, it was likely that of a Gible.

Name: GABITE
Pokedex: It has a range of possible habitats because it is the manifestation of a sinister force or aura and wherever that can be found, a Gabite likely will manifest.

Name: GARCHOMP
Pokedex: Some people report that based on recollections of their nightmares, a Garchomp was in the distance observing the subject suffer before they awaken.

Name: VULPIX
Pokedex: The stars on its tails are all in the form of various constellations.

Name: NINETALES
Pokedex: The rings around its neck are always gently rotating on an axis. The rotation is what helps this Pokemon orient itself when hit and keep its balance.

Name: T.BOUNSWEET
Pokedex: The flowers on its head secrete a noxious smelling liquid that can cause a variety of destabilizing effects from sleep to paralysis.

Name: T.STEENEE
Pokedex: Its spikes can be launched like projectiles and are often used to break down obstacles or tree branches that have fruits.

Name: T.TSAREENA
Pokedex: This Pokemon can remain perfectly still and pretend to be an innocuous flower. When its prey approaches, it can surprise it with its flower's large grip.

Name: PURRLOIN
Pokedex: Some say that if you cross its path, you will be doomed to bad luck for a day. However, its halo suggests otherwise.

Name: LIEPARD
Pokedex: This Pokemon is very limber and climb high elevations with ease. Its fur reflects the night sky.

Name: TOXEL
Pokedex: It lazes about for most of the day. It often uses a nearby branch to scratch itself rather than using its own hands.

Name: TOXTRICITY
Pokedex: This Pokemon is willing to challenge any Pokemon, even those much bigger to put on a spectacle. Are you not entertained?

Name: T.DEWPIDER
Pokedex: It has eyes covering its entire body, which enables it to have a full 360-degree field of vision.

Name: T.ARAQUANID
Pokedex: When it chitters, it is able to further intimidate and scare its foe because it is able to project its voice so it makes it seem like there are more nearby.

Name: GOOMY
Pokedex: These Pokemon appear in many different flavours: sour apple, cherry, blue razz, lemon, orange and grape. Can you collect them all?

Name: SLIGGOO
Pokedex: This Pokemon is very sticky and will decompose if it stays under the sun for too long.

Name: GOODRA
Pokedex: Every step it takes leaves a small part of itself behind. Not to worry because it quickly regenerates itself.

Name: MIME JR.
Pokedex: It busks on the side streets of large urban centres. The irony is that it is mute despite being a Sound type.

Name: MR. MIME
Pokedex: This Pokemon, along with Mime Jr. form small troupes to perform various circus acts to solicit donations from pedestrians in large urban centres.

Name: MR. RIME
Pokedex: It uses its prop walking cane and prop hat to really elevate its act to the next level because it is no longer confined to just using its hands and feet.

Name: T.DIGLETT
Pokedex: Alongside Cacnea and Voltorb, this Pokemon often gets confused as ordinary snow.

Name: T.DUGTRIO
Pokedex: A triplet of T. Digletts piled upon one another and then they froze over together in the current formation.

Name: LUVDISC
Pokedex: It wails for love that was long since lost that a crack has started to form across its body to reflect its heart break.

Name: SMEARGLE
Pokedex: It is often found in alleyways or urban centres experimenting with different art styles. It is considered a nuisance by local authorities.

Name: SHIELDON
Pokedex: Its head is said to be made of an ancient crystal that is as hard as steel.

Name: BASTIODON
Pokedex: Despite its unfortunate typing, the crystal wall on its head is able to be used to break almost any other naturally formed surface.

Name: APPLIN
Pokedex: It would ordinarily be able to roll around quite easily, however it is very noisy in doing so because the clamp gets dragged along with it.

Name: FLAPPLE
Pokedex: It is able to organize and mobilize other Pokemon towards a cause with little effort. Consequently, it was chained down because it is known to raise riots.

Name: APPLETUN
Pokedex: It is the brute force that is able to take a lot of hits. It acts as a sort of enforcer to threaten other Pokemon that annoy their leader.

Name: MIMIKYU
Pokedex: Rumours have claimed that this is not a disguise of Munchlax at all, but the Mimikyu has actually possessed it altogether.

Name: WOOLOO
Pokedex: Its "wool", if it can even be called that, is made of hardened boulders. The rocks are almost impenetrable.

Name: DUBWOOL
Pokedex: When this Pokemon is angry, it starts charging without control. The unfortunate victim of a hit will likely be permanently maimed.

Name: T.ABSOL
Pokedex: Rumour has it that this Pokemon is able to see the future and uses it for combat superiority.

Name: SNIVY
Pokedex: This friendly spirit wants nothing but to reach afterlife. It poses no threat whatsoever.

Name: SERVINE
Pokedex: People over the centuries have grown afraid for naught of this Pokemon. It is slowly, but surely losing its friendly demeanor.

Name: SERPERIOR
Pokedex: This enraged Pokemon is sick and tired of people causing harm to its species, so now it reacts violently to anything that approaches its kin.

Name: FENNEKIN
Pokedex: This little Pokemon has a plethora of potential hidden inside of it. However, it does not know yet whether to use it selflessly or not...

Name: BRAIXEN
Pokedex: After undergoing rigorous training, this Pokemon is able to talk to the dead using any reflective surface, albeit for a short period of time.

Name: DELPHOX
Pokedex: This ancient Pokemon is thought to be only a myth. It stores so much power inside its glass orb it is said it can communicate with the underworld freely.

Name: T.VOLTORB
Pokedex: It is the beginning of a small planet and is accreting matter to grow in size and density. It will eventually be able to generate its own gravitational force.

Name: T.ELECTRODE
Pokedex: When it evolved, it triggered a chemical transformation which amplified its gravitational force, attracting small objects into orbit.

Name: SNOVER
Pokedex: It is often mistaken for a smaller palm tree. Attempting to take the berries that it grows will result in it swiftly biting your fingers off.

Name: ABOMASNOW
Pokedex: The long leaves it grows can provide comfortable shade against the harshest sun. They are often found on beaches and desert oases alike.

Name: T.EXEGGCUTE
Pokedex: This Pokemon is often confused for being ordinary scorching embers because it is so small. They are defenseless when singled out.

Name: T.EXEGGUTOR
Pokedex: Its body is always scorching hot such that it is constantly spewing clouds of sulfuric gas from the volcano on its head.

Name: T.SABLEYE
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon scrounges on dead algae on the sea floor or in dark underwater caves because it is incapable of hunting well for itself.

Name: TRUBBISH
Pokedex: Have you ever thrown away your batteries in the garbage instead of recycling properly? Well guess what, youâ€™re to blame for the rise of these nasty Trubbish!

Name: GARBODOR
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon eats electrical waste. For this reason, much of its body exhibits a persistent electrical current that hovers around it.

Name: T.SWABLU
Pokedex: When these Pokemon giggle, it will create a nearby thunderclap, so whatever you do, do not tickle them!

Name: T.ALTARIA
Pokedex: These Altaria fly into stormy clouds to attract lightning as a means of healing themselves and boosting their own power.

Name: T.SLUGMA
Pokedex: This Pokemon is very small and found along the sea floor or in small ponds. It will suck up dead algae that have fallen to the bottom of the sea floor as food.

Name: T.MAGCARGO
Pokedex: Apparently, the slime that this Pokemon oozes can create some serious hallucinations. People often use it as an inexpensive way of getting high.

Name: T.MUDKIP
Pokedex: It has very precious crystals encrusted in its skin. As it is the weakest of its evolutionary line, poachers often hunt these Pokemon first.

Name: T.MARSHTOMP
Pokedex: When deep in a cave, if you see a light where you don not know where its source is coming from, it is likely from a T.Marshtomp.

Name: T.SWAMPERT
Pokedex: It can send a barrage of jagged crystals at its enemies if sent into a rage.

Name: CHESPIN
Pokedex: It burrows deep in the ground of caves. It will emerge when it needs to find food.

Name: QUILLADIN
Pokedex: It uses the crystals on its back as a light source to help it navigate through dark areas.

Name: CHESNAUGHT
Pokedex: If one of its crystals are taken away without permission, it can go into a rampage that can cause nearby tremors.

Name: FROAKIE
Pokedex: When it thunder storms, this Pokemon attracts lightning and is not remotely fazed by it. In fact, it quite enjoys it!

Name: FROGADIER
Pokedex: When this Pokemon hops, it gives off small sparks. It is very quick when it does dash around that can make it look like the ground is lit up with an electrical current.

Name: GRENINJA
Pokedex: This Pokemon is able to materialize and throw lightning bolts from a distance.

Name: JANGMO-O
Pokedex: This Pokemon keeps a sword safely sheathed away near its tail that it can use as a weapon.

Name: HAKAMO-O
Pokedex: This Pokemon is an adept warrior that it is able to use its sword, its tail, or its claws as weapons, all with equal proficiency.

Name: KOMMO-O
Pokedex: This Pokemon adorns itself with a headress that reflects its triumphs in combat. The longer its headress, the more fearsome it is.

Name: SCRAGGY
Pokedex: This Pokemon often inhabits the urban centres and hideaway areas. It is often sharing its mix tape with others in hopes of catching its "big break".

Name: SCRAFTY
Pokedex: This Pokemon has been recognized for its skill in hip-hop that it adorns itself in the best looking urban streetwear there is to be found.

Name: T.CHIKORITA
Pokedex: This Pokemon has electrical currents swirling from its antennae that it can channel and redirect in any direction it chooses.

Name: T.BAYLEEF
Pokedex: When it thunder storms, this Pokemon can use the electrical rod on its head to attract certain electrical attacks.

Name: T.MEGANIUM
Pokedex: This Pokemon is able to redirect electrical attacks using the circular field around its neck or absorb it to empower itself.

Name: T.CYNDAQUIL
Pokedex: Because of this Pokemon's small stature, it tries to keep a low profile. If it is startled, the ice on its back glistens brightly.

Name: T.QUILAVA
Pokedex: It can curl into a ball such that it is able to present itself as a natural formation of ice crystals.

Name: T.TYPHLOSION
Pokedex: The crystal on its body is hardened to be almost as tough as diamonds.

Name: T.TOTODILE
Pokedex: It is said that this Pokemon abounds in the underworld and its fire is from an ethereal plane.

Name: T.CROCONAW
Pokedex: It is unclear if the "flame" on its back is really fire, or a malicious force that has manifested.

Name: T.FERALIGATR
Pokedex: When the fire on its body flares, you can distinctly hear wailing noises.

Name: T.SURSKIT
Pokedex: It masks itself as a seed of a larger fruit but it is actually a scavenger that likes to eat a lot of that fruit.

Name: T.MASQUERAIN
Pokedex: The leaves on its wings remain as an autumn colour, regardless of the season.

Name: T.STANTLER
Pokedex: It is constantly channeling an electrical current between the two nodes on its head, even when it is asleep.

Name: CLAMPERL
Pokedex: This Pokemon is in a perpetual state of fear that it has sealed itself off in a psychic bubble. It is terrified of bugs and of the darkness in particular.

Name: HUNTAIL
Pokedex: This Pokemon lives in the abyssal depths of the ocean; put your hand too close to its mouth and you risk losing it.

Name: GOREBYSS
Pokedex: This pokemon lives in vast schools consisting of thousands of members. It is the common prey of Wailmer and Wailord.

Name: KLINK
Pokedex: This Pokemon has an internal clock that allows it to keep time so you do not need to carry around a watch or check your phone to confirm the time.

Name: KLANG
Pokedex: It is able to synchronize its attacks based on the internal clock that allows it to amplify its damage.

Name: KLINKLANG
Pokedex: When it is perfectly synchronized, the bells on Klinklang will ring to let you know.

Name: DARUMAKA
Pokedex: It is known for starting noisy riots in the jungle whether it be from pounding its chest or screeching from the treetops.

Name: DARMANITAN
Pokedex: It is known for getting into screeching matches with the Primeape family. Get ear protection and take cover when you see this happen.

Name: T.SKITTY
Pokedex: A T. Skitty is very protective of the weed on its tail. It is rumoured that if a strong breeze blows it away, the Skitty will also perish.

Name: T.DELCATTY
Pokedex: While the weed always remains aesthetically pleasing, larger ones can start to slow down and cause back problems for certain older T. Delcatties.

Name: T.DODUO
Pokedex: It will immerse itself up to its waist in water at most to hunt for fish. It usually does not like wading in further despite being a Water-type.

Name: T.DODRIO
Pokedex: It is very vain but very affectionate. If you pet it, you need to know exactly how or else it will jab you with one of its beaks.

Name: T.NUMEL
Pokedex: Its breath can crystallize the air around it into snowflakes.

Name: T.CAMERUPT
Pokedex: The mountain on its back is able to create small localized snow squalls that make it snow around it.

Name: BINACLE
Pokedex: Its latent psychic power allows it to levitate a number of rocks and sediment around it as a way to show off.

Name: BARBARACLE
Pokedex: It has reached a level of psychic mastery that it is capable of attacking from afar and anticipating enemy attacks because it has seen into the future.

Name: ARROKUDA
Pokedex: This Pokemon is bitter tasting and any unfortunate bird Pokemon that ends up eating it will have to contend with a bad stomach ache that follows shortly after.

Name: BARRASKEWDA
Pokedex: The aura that this Pokemon emanates serves as a bit of a warning to any bird Pokemon that fancies it a delicious snack.

Name: T.MACHOP
Pokedex: This Pokemon is beginning to tap into its psychic potential. As a result, its stand is weakly formed and highly transparent.

Name: T.MACHOKE
Pokedex: Its psychic capabilities have advanced, allowing it to manifest a more opaque stand but it still requires further meditation to fully ascend.

Name: T.MACHAMP
Pokedex: This Pokemon is so spiritually in-tune that it is able to channel a fully corporeal stand to demonstrate its combat prowess.
