Name: SMOOCHUM
Pokedex: Its voice cracks easily when it tries to reach high notes. It is still training its voice but it has a long way to go.

Name: JYNX
Pokedex: Its voice is able to reach very high notes effortlessly. However, it has learned to be conscious of when and where it sings this way, for fear of causing avalanches.

Name: ZIGZAGOON
Pokedex: Zigzagoons are ordinarily not strong enough to hunt by themselves and instead feast on what is discarded by stronger predators in their habitat.

Name: LINOONE
Pokedex: The spots that form on its skin are from its poor dietary choices it made as a Zigzagoon.

Name: OBSTAGOON
Pokedex: It has finally become strong enough to mobilize a pack of Zigzagoons and Linoones. It acts as a type of "alpha" to lead their pack.

Name: INDEEDEE
Pokedex: It is a creature that has been banished to isolated areas such as swamps and sewers. Apparently, simply touching it can result in catching a virulent plague.

Name: CRANIDOS
Pokedex: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with headbutts.

Name: RAMPARDOS
Pokedex: Its skull is as hard as iron. It is a brute that tears down jungle trees while catching prey.

Name: T.GIBLE
Pokedex: T.Gibles are able to speed through the water faster than most other Pokemon at its level.

Name: T.GABITE
Pokedex: T.Gabites are able to perform various tricks and often included as part of circus troupes for aquatic stunts.

Name: T.GARCHOMP
Pokedex: When a T.Garchomp is chasing prey, it is able to charge through rocks and cleanly cut them in half because of their jagged fins.

Name: T.YANMA
Pokedex: This Pokemon is made of a fine aluminum alloy. If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

Name: T.YANMEGA
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon is able to beat its wings quickly that it can create sound waves with such force that can actually knock back a person.

Name: REMORAID
Pokedex: This Pokemon can zip around in water because it is able to use the electrical energy it generates to give it a speed boost.

Name: OCTILLERY
Pokedex: This Pokemon is able to latch on to prey and use its electrically charged tentacles to electrocute its prey into submission.

Name: MISDREAVUS
Pokedex: This Pokemon is able to sing heavenly choirs. Once you have heard its refrains, you feel more pure.

Name: MISMAGIUS
Pokedex: It is said that this Pokemon is able to sing certain songs that have healing properties and can cure certain diseases.

Name: POLIWAG
Pokedex: This Pokemon loves mud. If it is away from mud or water for too long however, its skin goes dry and cracks.

Name: POLIWHIRL
Pokedex: Poliwhirl are extremely territorial, and produce deep loud bellows to each other to signal their territory. However, they have a soft spot for Poliwag.

Name: POLIWRATH
Pokedex: These pokemon are a king of their local ecosytem. Even though they are known as kings, they will not hesitate to raze their territory during a fight with a rival.

Name: POLITOED
Pokedex: Politoed wields the legendary sword, Masamune. It seeks to avenge its fallen comrade by defeating Lucario.

Name: PHANTUMP
Pokedex: When this Pokemon was first seen burning, it was said to be a message from a god.

Name: TREVENANT
Pokedex: This Pokemon is able to spontaneously start burning and suppress the flames at will.

Name: TYROGUE
Pokedex: This Pokemon is said to be the alter-ego and secret identity of a famous superhero...

Name: HITMONLEE
Pokedex: This Pokemon is a superhero that is capable of flight and also uses psychic attacks from afar.

Name: HITMONCHAN
Pokedex: This Pokemon is a superhero that has super strength and moves quickly.

Name: HITMONTOP
Pokedex: This Pokemon is a superhero that has the ability to throw bolts of lightning with a bow.

Name: PINCURCHIN
Pokedex: They are soft to the touch, and and make a screeching sound when squeezed. Strangely, they are used to play the national anthem of a far off country.

Name: SCYTHER
Pokedex: Its blades are made of pure light, and are able to slice through virtually anything. Unfortunately, because of this it has issues picking up food.

Name: SCIZOR
Pokedex: Developed in an underground lab, this Pokemon has offensive power, but development was rushed as it is prone to overheating.

Name: PINSIR
Pokedex: This Pokemon exhibits such a strong degree of magnetism that the rocks that are encrusted in its body emit charged electricity.

Name: ROLYCOLY
Pokedex: Valuable minerals, gems and precious stones can be found in the rubble of its body.

Name: CARKOL
Pokedex: This Pokemon enjoys adding various precious minerals to its pile that it engages in drilling of its own.

Name: COALOSSAL
Pokedex: This Pokemon is often used by mining companies to accumulate stone and minerals and for its ability to sense other precious ores which improves yields.

Name: RIOLU
Pokedex: This Pokemon trains daily in honing its power in the mystic arts. It is thought that Riolu first appeared after falling from a wormhole to another dimension.

Name: LUCARIO
Pokedex: Lucario is from a civilisation of the distant past where magic was commonplace. It practices its dark arts with no mercy for others.

Name: TRAPINCH
Pokedex: It allows the small snow structure on its nose act as a trap. When potential prey approach, it will quickly snap at them.

Name: VIBRAVA
Pokedex: It frequently comes out in the early morning to feast on the bugs and other small critters that come out from the snow.

Name: FLYGON
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon hides in the heart of blizzards it creates and seldom appears where people can see it.

Name: DHELMISE
Pokedex: This Pokemon has managed to infest a manmade satellite and use it as a host body to travel quickly throughout outer space.

Name: T.GEODUDE
Pokedex: A spirit has possessed and empowered this Geodude giving it spectral powers.

Name: T.GRAVELER
Pokedex: This Pokemon emanates such strong spectral energy that it is able to use these ghostly powers to land attacks from afar.

Name: T.GOLEM
Pokedex: Touching this Pokemon will send a chill through your bones because it is a way for it to gradually siphon your life essence without you noticing.

Name: T.ROGGENROLA
Pokedex: This Pokemon moves by using its built in static energy to propel it in the direction it wants to go.

Name: T.BOLDORE
Pokedex: Its energy is dangerously unstable and it periodically gives off charged electrical novas that can fry electrical appliances.

Name: T.GIGALITH
Pokedex: This Pokemon carries so much latent energy that it is able to seamlessly connect multiple rocks together through an electrical current.

Name: T.VANILLITE
Pokedex: Its body can get so hot that sometimes, simple water is rendered ineffective against it and will just evaporate on contact.

Name: T.VANILLISH
Pokedex: The top of its head is constantly erupting and spewing out hot lava. Maintaining a safe distance from it is strongly advised.

Name: T.VANILLUXE
Pokedex: One of its heads spews only sulfur whereas the other spews lava. They are constantly competing with one another to see which substance is produced most.

Name: DRATINI
Pokedex: These Pokemon like to take naps on the highest clouds in the stratosphere.

Name: DRAGONAIR
Pokedex: In certain fables, these Pokemon were considered to be favoured pets of some of the gods.

Name: DRAGONITE
Pokedex: In certain fables, these Pokemon were considered to be some of the emissaries of the heavens because they were blessed with godly speed.

Name: T.MURKROW
Pokedex: They are often used as familiars to wizards so they pick up a fair bit of magical skill by themselves from their wizard masters.

Name: T.HONCHKROW
Pokedex: They have become adept at magic all by themselves that they are now wizard masters themselves and willing to take on apprentices.

Name: CLEFFA
Pokedex: They are very small and often confused with ordinary butterflies. They are responsible for casting certain enchantments in forests.

Name: CLEFAIRY
Pokedex: When their wings flutter, they spread pixie dust around them. In sufficient quantities, this can allow a person to be able to fly.

Name: CLEFABLE
Pokedex: It is said that if you manage to capture one, you can use the pixie dust it produces to make yourself exceptionally wealthy.

Name: T.KABUTO
Pokedex: This Pokemon is thought to be a cybernetic predator from a distant planet. It crash landed several million years ago.

Name: T.KABUTOPS
Pokedex: Its scythes are connected by a combination of some unknown energy, likely a technology that was founded on its home planet.

Name: ARCHEN
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon was successfully restored from a fossil. It was said that its wing flaps could cause thunder claps in ancient times.

Name: ARCHEOPS
Pokedex: Its feathers carry a significant amount of static electricity. In sufficient quantities, these feathers can be used to create chain lightning.

Name: TIRTOUGA
Pokedex: Its shell is nigh impenetrable, but its underbelly is vulnerable. If flipped over, this Pokemon will flail about trying to reposition itself.

Name: CARRACOSTA
Pokedex: This Pokemon is extremely defensive, being able to take explosions head-on without a scratch. A downside of this is that it struggles with mobility.

Name: DREEPY
Pokedex: This Pokemon has very small vents so it is unable to travel very long distances but more so sputters along the way.

Name: DRAKLOAK
Pokedex: Rather than seeking out immense speed, Drakloaks much prefer to perform tricks in the air and create various pictures in the cloud trails they form.

Name: DRAGAPULT
Pokedex: It draws in air from the vents on its head and expells it outward, creating a cloud trail that envelops its body while propelling it forwards.

Name: WIMPOD
Pokedex: It scurries around leaving a trail of poison as it passes. People should be careful of where they step as it can burn through the soles of their shoes.

Name: GOLISOPOD
Pokedex: It has evolved and become far more intimidating that the prey has now become the predator.

Name: MUNNA
Pokedex: This Pokemon needs regular security updates uploaded every Tuesday to ensure that it is protected against viruses on the Internet.

Name: MUSHARNA
Pokedex: This Pokemon is reaching terminal failure and its hard drive is now regularly crashing due to a virus infection.

Name: SHUPPET
Pokedex: This Pokemon is used to cheer up sick children in hospitals, however, many children have developed a fear of them instead.

Name: BANETTE
Pokedex: This Pokemon is used to produce entertainment for entitled royalty. It harbours a seething hatred for the court in which it performs.

Name: STONJOURNER
Pokedex: It is constantly playing music from its loud speakers. It can be very obnoxious and disruptive for this reason.

Name: T.LAPRAS
Pokedex: This Pokemon has allegedly existed since prehistoric times. It towers over other Pokemon as it lumbers through the savannah at its own pace.

Name: T.WOOLOO
Pokedex: They are regularly farmed as the bushes on these Pokemon are constantly bearing berries and fruits.

Name: T.DUBWOOL
Pokedex: To diversify the type of berries it grows, a Dubwool will ram into trees that grow those kind until they fall into their bush, which they then learn to grow themselves.

Name: BIDOOF
Pokedex: It likes to build small structures on water using logs, tree branches, and leaves.

Name: BIBAREL
Pokedex: If you tickle the male species, it will drop a bunch of the shiny things it has collected. If you tickle the female, the baby in its pouch will likely bite you.

Name: DRILBUR
Pokedex: While it is blind, it uses sonic waves to find its way and navigate through caves and deep tunnels.

Name: EXCADRILL
Pokedex: As it uses sound waves when digging, its spines help shield it from danger in case the sound waves it sends out misleads it.

Name: T.DRILBUR
Pokedex: When light beams bounce off this Pokemon, it can produce and warp the colours into colourful displays.

Name: T.EXCADRILL
Pokedex: It uses the crystals on its head and arms to help it dig through caves. They are capable of emitting their own light to help it navigate.

Name: SNOM
Pokedex: Due to its small stature, it hides under rocks to avoid detection. If it is found, it uses its adorable appearance to convince predators to spare it.

Name: FROSMOTH
Pokedex: There is a fairytale about an old claymaker that fashioned this Frosmoth, and it was brought to life because of a wish he made during a shooting star.

Name: HOUNDOUR
Pokedex: It was a noble animal in life, and the best friend that humans can have. What? Can you not see its halo?

Name: HOUNDOOM
Pokedex: It is said that man's best friend will meet you in heaven when it passes on. It's actually quite a tragic story.

Name: PIPLUP
Pokedex: It is not very good at walking and falls over easily. When it falls behind its group, it needs to quickly waddle to catch up.

Name: PRINPLUP
Pokedex: They are strong divers and often hunt for small fish Pokemon in freezing waters.

Name: EMPOLEON
Pokedex: It is the leader of a small colony of Piplup and Prinplup. Each colony usually only has one male Empoleon as the king and one female as the queen.

Name: T.SOLOSIS
Pokedex: They are small parasites from interstellar space. They lie in wait underground until they can evolve.

Name: T.DUOSION
Pokedex: When it has siphoned enough energy from its surroundings, it evolves and migrates to continue its parasitic lifecycle.

Name: T.REUNICLUS
Pokedex: It is actually an interstellar parasite that consume the resources from the planet and then summarily migrate onto the next world.

Name: MUDBRAY
Pokedex: This Pokemon is often used to teach children how to ride horse Pokemon because they are smaller and easier to climb on.

Name: MUDSDALE
Pokedex: This Pokemon are groomed to be race horses or for beauty competitions because their braids are some of the most beautiful of any other Pokemon.

Name: CRAMORANT
Pokedex: This Pokemon can drill into trees to find small bugs in the cores of trees. They have an annoying habit of starting their pecking very early in the morning.

Name: T.HOPPIP
Pokedex: Due to its small stature, a light gust is usually enough to blow it away.

Name: T.SKIPLOOM
Pokedex: When it is eating, the lights on its antenna flicker periodically.

Name: T.JUMPLUFF
Pokedex: It is able to produce its own light source significant enough that it does not need to chase other lights like other moth Pokemon do.

Name: SEWADDLE
Pokedex: It observes from a distance and studies its foes. When it is ready, it will adapt and change its form to perfectly replicate its enemy.

Name: SWADLOON
Pokedex: Dark energies swirl beneath the cowl of its robe, undetectable by most. It harbours sinister energy from a galaxy far far away.

Name: LEAVANNY
Pokedex: Its arm blades are composed completely of laser energy. They are raised from youth to become adept warriors.

Name: WHISMUR
Pokedex: It just enjoys vibing. Nothing and no one will stop it from having a good time.

Name: LOUDRED
Pokedex: This Pokemon is the life of the party. It can drop a sick beat and has better moves than most humans.

Name: EXPLOUD
Pokedex: This Pokemon likes to constantly yell "Turn down for what?!" for some reason.

Name: SIZZLIPEDE
Pokedex: Despite its small stature, it is feared by many predators because if it's going down, it will use its poison to take its predator down with it.

Name: CENTISKORCH
Pokedex: When confronted by a predator, it is able to move all of its legs to make it seem more imposing. If that doesn't work, it will resort to its poison.

Name: SOBBLE
Pokedex: During thunderstorms, this Pokemon will play its flute to soothe nearby Pokemon that get upset from the thunderstorms.

Name: DRIZZILE
Pokedex: This Pokemon is looking for its big break, in the hope that someone will recognize its musical ability.

Name: INTELEON
Pokedex: There is a fable that this Pokemon used its flute to attract Rattata away from a town for a fee. When the town did not pay, it lured the children of the town away.

Name: T.TIMBURR
Pokedex: It is small and stupid. It often bashes its head against tree trunks for amusement.

Name: T.GURDURR
Pokedex: They are big and bulky because of constantly carrying around large logs of wood. They are able to effortlessly bench press the log.

Name: T.CONKELDURR
Pokedex: It is very lovable but it must be taught to restrain its affection because it doesn't realize that squeezing a person between its logs can kill them.

Name: CORPHISH
Pokedex: It congregates along beaches and show off by crushing progressively larger rocks in its pincers to attract potential mates.

Name: CRAWDAUNT
Pokedex: It often groups in small bands along seashores and coves. In large enough groups, they are used to raid local fishing villages.

Name: CARNIVINE
Pokedex: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

Name: ANORITH
Pokedex: Despite their small stature, the venom from its pincers were said to be able to incapacitate much larger predators.

Name: ARMALDO
Pokedex: In prehistoric times, Armaldo would use the boulders on their back to provide them with shelter from the scorching sun.

Name: BAGON
Pokedex: This Pokemon is a playful creature by nature, but it needs to be reined in because it can inadvertently start large fires if it gets up to too much trouble.

Name: SHELGON
Pokedex: The molten shell on its body should not be allowed to cool otherwise it will become significantly weighed down and immobilize it under the weight.

Name: SALAMENCE
Pokedex: It is rumoured that this is not even its final form, and it can transform into a much more fearsome multi-headed creature.

Name: MUNCHLAX
Pokedex: Its fur is very thick that despite living in very cold habitats, it doesn't feel cold.

Name: SNORLAX
Pokedex: As it hibernates, it has honed its psychic powers to be able to retrieve objects from afar without resorting to have to get up and move.

Name: T.LARVESTA
Pokedex: It is said to be a Pokemon from a different galaxy altogether, and it actually managed to travel here by opening a wormhole.

Name: T.VOLCARONA
Pokedex: Rumour has it that its wings each provide a snapshot of a nearby galaxy, and every pair of wings on a T.Volcarona are a unique part of the universe.

Name: TEPIG
Pokedex: This Pokemon couldn't be happier than when it's frolicking in a puddle of mud.

Name: PIGNITE
Pokedex: This Pokemon loves cannonballing into large pools of mud. It attempts to curl up and make as big a splash as it can right after a rainfall.

Name: EMBOAR
Pokedex: This Pokemon has jagged rocks that are encrusted into its skin around its torso. It can take these jagged rocks and fling them at enemies.

Name: SNEASEL
Pokedex: A Sneasel adorns its face with face painting in hunting parties to appear more threatening. In groups, they can quickly surround and overwhelm their prey.

Name: WEAVILE
Pokedex: Scientists are able to evaluate the age of a subject Weavile simply by assessing the length of its branches.

Name: MILCERY
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon is the toxic residue that manifests near locations rich in fossil fuels. Its body is very hot to the touch.

Name: ALCREMIE
Pokedex: This Pokemon typically loiters near oil drilling locations as it feeds on the tailings produced from mining activities to gradually become larger.

Name: FRILLISH
Pokedex: They are very mischievous Pokemon because they often like to expel their spores when people wander by to infect them with a poison or paralyzing agent.

Name: JELLICENT
Pokedex: The gunk that accumulates under its mushroom head mix with the Pokemon's natural spores to make it extremely poisonous. It should be handled with care.

Name: CLOBBOPUS
Pokedex: This Pokemon's tentacles are so strong that many other foes do not dare try to challenge it for food when hunting.

Name: GRAPPLOCT
Pokedex: This Pokemon lives deep in the ocean. With its tentacles, it has been able to crush smaller ships and bring them down to the sea floor.

Name: T.NOSEPASS
Pokedex: It is often used as a portable light source but its stubby legs means it often needs to be carried around since it can't usually keep up with walking speed.

Name: T.PROBOPASS
Pokedex: Using its cable arms, it is capable of plugging itself into electrical appliances to recharge them.

Name: CUFANT
Pokedex: This Pokemon is too lazy to reach for fruit in trees despite its long trunk so it instead uses its psychic powers to telepathically retrieve the fruit.

Name: COPPERAJAH
Pokedex: In marital ceremonies among island tribes, this Pokemon often carries the bride and groom up and down the aisle.

Name: BLITZLE
Pokedex: Blitzle's fur is freeing and lightweight, allowing them to have an extra aerodynamic boost and reach incredible speeds when running.

Name: ZEBSTRIKA
Pokedex: Its mane is soft and highly coveted by poachers. However, poachers have been unsuccessful in being able to catch it because of how fast it is.

Name: SLAKOTH
Pokedex: This Pokemon is said to hibernate throughout the year. It's not clear how this is possible.

Name: VIGOROTH
Pokedex: When this Pokemon was first fed a Chople Berry, it said in response "fam, this berry tastes low key sus af tho fr ong"

Name: SLAKING
Pokedex: This Pokemon is quick to anger when it is awoken from its sleep or hungry. Many dare not to disturb it.

Name: MILTANK
Pokedex: It is often raised by farmers to produce highly nutritious milk. It sometimes has a bad habit of grazing on the wreath that grows on its neck.

Name: HELIOPTILE
Pokedex: The small snakes on this Pokemon's head are an extension of its body. Their fangs seep venom and the poison can paralyze a foe ten times its size.

Name: HELIOLISK
Pokedex: The snakes on this Pokemon's head are capable of turning their target to stone, significantly lowering their speed, making hunting easy.

Name: HATENNA
Pokedex: This Pokemon is known for living an isolated life in locations far away from civilization. For that reason, it is often misunderstood.

Name: HATTREM
Pokedex: This Pokemon is known for being able to sing haunting songs or cast spells that can inflict terror on their target rendering them immobile.

Name: HATTERENE
Pokedex: This Pokemon's knowledge of the arcane arts dips into forbidden magic. It was cast out from society for practicing the dark arts.

Name: T.SWINUB
Pokedex: If you must pet this Pokemon, it prefers that the leaves on its head are scratched versus being rubbed on its belly.

Name: T.PILOSWINE
Pokedex: When grazing, it can keep perfectly still that it is often mistaken as a hedge or a small bush.

Name: T.MAMOSWINE
Pokedex: This Pokemon will often bash its head against larger trees in an effort to knock down the fruits that grow on them.

Name: CHINGLING
Pokedex: It emits a small electromagnetic charge that can cause signal disturbances to nearby electrical devices.

Name: CHIMECHO
Pokedex: It emits its electrical field whenever it meets a stranger to protect itself. It will only lower the field when it trusts that person.

Name: T.MAGNEMITE
Pokedex: A T.Magnemite's core contains a variety of crystals, some of which are extremely valuable, leading it to being hunted to near extinction as a result.

Name: T.MAGNETON
Pokedex: T.Magneton form when 3 T.Magnemite psychically fuse together. The dominant one can be identified by having an extra crystal on its body.

Name: T.MAGNEZONE
Pokedex: T.Magnezone act as colony protectors of smaller T.Magnemites. They will often attempt to blind any attackers with violent beams of light.

Name: T.IMPIDIMP
Pokedex: It is rumoured to have spawned in the fires of the underworld and has somehow made its way to the mortal plane.

Name: T.MORGREM
Pokedex: It is very protective of the embers in its hand. It is rumoured that it is actually the soul it received from making a bargain with a greedy human.

Name: T.GRIMMSNARL
Pokedex: They are rumoured to be the torturers of evil people when they make their way to the underworld. They enjoy using fire in their punishments.

Name: DEDENNE
Pokedex: Poking this Pokemon in different places elicits different squeals. It is a toy that is highly coveted by small children, but very annoying for parents.

Name: T.BUDEW
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon attempts to stay hidden or tries to camouflage itself near densely populated trees until it is ready to bloom as that is when it evolves.

Name: T.ROSELIA
Pokedex: The thorns on this Pokemon can cause very deep gashes. Even experienced florists need to be very careful when handling this Pokemon.

Name: T.ROSERADE
Pokedex: This Pokemon exudes an entrancing aroma that can cause a number of side effects ranging from lulling targets to sleep or causing seizures!

Name: LOTAD
Pokedex: This PokÃ©mon lives in deserts and masquerades as an ordinary cactus to hide from predators while is is still young.

Name: LOMBRE
Pokedex: This Pokemon thrives in intense sunlight. It retains fresh water so lost wanderers in the desert will typically ask it for water when they are thirsty.

Name: LUDICOLO
Pokedex: This Pokemon can launch its barbs in a volley at an enemy when annoyed. Its happy-go-lucky attitude should not be taken for granted.

Name: WATTREL
Pokedex: It is very fast and is able to launch sharpened projectiles from its wings to maim its prey and close the distance on them quickly so they cannot escape.

Name: KILOWATTREL
Pokedex: It is an endangered Pokemon but it has found refuge by nesting atop tall mountains in cold climates to discourage intruders from attacking its young.

Name: WYRDEER
Pokedex: Despite the appearance of frost accumulating on its leaves, the berries it grows on its bushes are highly nutritious and sought after by berry enthusiasts.

Name: T.WYRDEER
Pokedex: It is often found on mountains or similar high elevation areas during thunderstorms because it enjoys attracting lightning with its antlers.

Name: ANNIHILAPE
Pokedex: It has become unstable and frayed from its relentless screeching. Its persistence is one of its most admirable but also most despised qualities.

Name: FINIZEN
Pokedex: Its curiosity often leads it to wander easily as it follows ships before it realizes that it has been separated from the rest of its pod.

Name: PALAFIN
Pokedex: It is often used by sailors to scout ahead and use its horn to help break down large ice formations to help assist ships navigate past hazardous areas.

Name: PORYGON
Pokedex: It has a malevolent nature and feeds off the software it sabotages. However, it quickly retreats on detecting anti-malware.

Name: PORYGON2
Pokedex: Once it is able to access a computer, it can quickly spread across other connected systems. It lies in wait to sabotage at the right moment.

Name: PORYGON-Z
Pokedex: Its ability to distort and corrupt data allows it to warp spacetime around itself, causing glitches in the fabric of reality.

Name: URSALUNA
Pokedex: It is able to shift from a corporeal form to ethereal form at will, which it uses to its advantage for hunting.

Name: PAWMI
Pokedex: It is normally very reserved and doesn't like strangers, but when it warms up to a person, it will become one of its best friends.

Name: PAWMO
Pokedex: It is very skittish and loud noises tend to scare it easily. It tries to be brave but it often will run in fear.

Name: PAWMOT
Pokedex: Petting this Pokemon on its tuft of hair is the best way to show it affection. It does not like being pet on its tail so avoid that at all costs.

Name: FUECOCO
Pokedex: It tends to sleep on land at night, but will hunt for fish in ponds and rivers within jungles, swamps and desert oases.

Name: CROCALOR
Pokedex: It often curls up into a ball to pretend to be a rock to attract unsuspecting bugs. It can then quickly spring into action to surprise its meal.

Name: SKELEDIRGE
Pokedex: Its tail often betrays its ability to surprise its prey, thus it prefers to hunt in rivers where it won't be spotted until it's too late.

Name: TINKATINK
Pokedex: It likes to make various sculptures using the bones it collects. It's unclear where it finds all these bones to begin with.

Name: TINKATUFF
Pokedex: It hunts in small parties for dragons. Individually, they are not very threatening, but in a small band, they can outnumber and overwhelm a foe.

Name: TINKATON
Pokedex: It swings around the skeleton of an ancient dragon. Some say the skeleton itself is sentient.

Name: T.FEEBAS
Pokedex: This Pokemon enjoys frolicking in hot lava, as a result, its population has grown significantly because it has no natural predators in this habitat.

Name: T.MILOTIC
Pokedex: This Pokemon tends to attract lava to its skin that will rapidly cool and slow it down when it sleeps, so it tends to only take quick naps.

Name: SNEASLER
Pokedex: This Pokemon is distrusting of outsiders. It is viewed as the tribal warrior leader that directs other Weaviles and Sneasels in battle.

Name: SKARMORY
Pokedex: A PokÃ©mon that has wings made of jagged rocks. While it is unable to fly, these wings give it an aerodynamic boost, allowing it to run very fast.

Name: WOOPER
Pokedex: This Pokemon is viewed as a lucky charm. It tends to play near geysers and can sense when they are about to erupt.

Name: QUAGSIRE
Pokedex: This Pokemon is viewed as very wise in folk tales, but in reality, it actually has very low intelligence.

Name: FLABÃ©BÃ©
Pokedex: This Pokemon has made a sort of nest in a coral bed and gotten very attached to it but it can walk away at any time.

Name: FLOETTE
Pokedex: This Pokemon carries around a part of its coral bed around with it wherever it goes.

Name: FLORGES
Pokedex: This Pokemon is rooted in place, so it prefers to not move around often as it is very onerous to move its entire coral bed around with it.

Name: EMOLGA
Pokedex: They are very naughty Pokemon and enjoy nosediving from steep heights and swarming lost travellers and hikers.

Name: SALANDIT
Pokedex: It is able to dim the fluorescent sacs on its skin to conceal itself from predators in deep sea and underwater caves.

Name: SALAZZLE
Pokedex: It is able to leap and surprise attack a foe, and electrocute its prey using those sacs on its skin.

Name: DUDUNSPARCE
Pokedex: While it has evolved and developed a longer body, if it finds a suitable host, it will not hesitate to abandon this carapace in favour of the new host body.

Name: HOOPA
Pokedex: This Pokemon will often prank people and then use its magic to disappear before being caught.

Name: GIMMIGHOUL
Pokedex: This Pokemon lives inside a mound of soil. As it grows, it collects more soil to build its mound.

Name: GHOLDENGO
Pokedex: It is made up of a number of Gimmighoul that live in a mound together. They work together in unison to both attack and defend the colony.

Name: DELIBIRD
Pokedex: The log that you commonly find them sleeping on is actually their tail. Despite their size they can swing it very adeptly in battle.

Name: DIPPLIN
Pokedex: It will find crafty ways to escape its sentence, not limited to digging holes, or corroding away the steel bars that imprison it.

Name: BASCULEGION
Pokedex: This Pokemon is able to blend into the water that the ripples it creates are indistinguishable from wind blowing across the water.

Name: TAPU KOKO
Pokedex: Legends that say this PokÃ©mon is the vengeful spirit of a large spider that guarded the woods. Any who search for it are lost forever.

Name: TAPU LELE
Pokedex: Stories say this Pokemon offers to guide lost travellers in a jungle, but actually it seeks to lure them deeper only to steal their supplies.

Name: TAPU BULU
Pokedex: Tales say this Pokemon brings destruction wherever it goes due to the heat it emanates. It can turn lush areas into barren, scorched ruins.

Name: TAPU FINI
Pokedex: The myth is that this Pokemon is the embodiment of a multi-headed snake that guarded the mountains and could turn people into stone.

Name: ETERNATUS
Pokedex: A Pokemon that passed away a long time ago. It was revived through the collection of its various bones that were scattered across the region.

Name: MANAPHY
Pokedex: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

Name: DIALGA
Pokedex: It has the power to control time. It is one of the Creation Trio of the Multiverse.

Name: PALKIA
Pokedex: It has the ability to distort space. It is one of the Creation Trio of the Multiverse.

Name: GIRATINA
Pokedex: A PokÃ©mon that was imprisoned in the In-Between by his brothers, Dialga and Palkia. He is the Lord of the Antimatter Realm.

Name: ARCEUS
Pokedex: The Father of Creation. It is described in mythology as the PokÃ©mon that shaped the multiverse with the Creation Trio.
